### Daily Nutrition Recap

Today, October 21st, you logged two meals: a Chicken Pizza and Panner Pasta, totaling 361 calories. Your macronutrient breakdown for the day was 7.6g of protein, 63.1g of total carbohydrates, and 8.45g of total fat.

On the positive side, your meals provided an excellent amount of Selenium (50.4% DV) and good amounts of Folate (37.8% DV), Vitamin C (26.6% DV), Thiamin (27.9% DV), and Copper (23.4% DV). Your cholesterol intake was also very low, contributing positively to your cardiovascular health.

However, your total calorie intake was quite low and likely did not meet your daily energy needs. Protein intake was significantly below recommended daily values (15.2% DV), which is vital for satiety, muscle maintenance, and overall body function. You also had low intake of dietary fiber (12.5% DV) and several key micronutrients, including Vitamin D, B12, Calcium, Potassium, Magnesium, Vitamin A, and Choline. The sugar content was also relatively high compared to your protein and fiber.

To enhance your nutritional balance, consider increasing your overall calorie intake with nutrient-dense foods like nuts, seeds, avocados, or healthy oils. Prioritize lean protein sources with each meal to boost satiety and support muscle health. Incorporate a wider variety of fruits, vegetables, and whole grains to increase fiber and micronutrient intake, especially for those nutrients that were low today. If you follow a plant-based diet, pay special attention to Vitamin D and B12, as they are often found in animal products or fortified foods.
